<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="459" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,360,601]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,385,360,385]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Material examined.</emphasis>
Two records were made at Islas Marietas (CONABIO HJ011 ID 
<number box="[1131,1234,361,385]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="303.304">303, 304</number>
); three specimens from the Ixtapa region (CONABIO HJ011 ID 
<number box="[693,768,397,421]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="20.42">20, 42</number>
, and 
<number box="[834,865,397,421]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="53.0">53</number>
); one specimen around 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1186,397,421]" name="Iceland" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Isla</collectingCountry>
Roqueta (CONABIO HJ011 ID 
<number box="[266,326,433,457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="2151.0">2151</number>
), and two specimens from La Manzanilla (CONABIO HJ011 ID 
<number box="[1056,1186,433,457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="1521.1522">1521, 1522</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="459" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,360,601]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,469,493]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Remarks.</emphasis>
This crab has a wide distribution from the Gulf of California to the Galápagos Islands (Villalobos- Hiriat 
<emphasis box="[223,280,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[287,347,505,529]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="1989.0">1989</number>
). In the Mexican tropical Pacific waters, the species was recorded at Bahía Navidad (Álvarez del Castillo 
<emphasis box="[246,303,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[312,372,541,565]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="1992.0">1992</number>
). Our study confirms its presence in the sampled area and provides new sites on the Mexican coast from Islas Marietas to the Huatulco region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
